id: ADR-001
kind: ADR
title: ADR-001: Why this example uses React and TOON-first documentation
status: accepted
scope: app
owner: Architecture
date: 2026-03-03
canonicalKey: todo-app-adr-frontend
tags[3]: decision,frontend,docs
dependsOn[1]: DOMAINTREE-001
supersedes[0]:
supersededBy[0]:
conflictsWith[0]:
sections[4]{title,body}:
  Context,The example must be obvious to a broad audience and quick to run while demonstrating planning artifacts.
  Decision,Use React with TypeScript and Vite for familiarity and local state with all documentation in .toon.
  Alternatives,Plain JavaScript was rejected for weaker typing and higher onboarding cost with no clear benefit.
  Consequences,The stack is approachable and demonstrates the workflow but lacks backend persistence.